        <V n="text" t="single">
          <T n="single">0x75DF41C8<!--String: "Oh, thanks for writing back. It’s funny, I’d thought so much about how maybe I should just change to be more like a person they'd want me to be. After all, don't we all undergo a lot of changes over time?\n\nI think about how butterflies will go and spend a lot of their lives in one stage only to have us think mainly of what they look like when they emerge from a chrysalis. The weirdest thing about feeling alone is that when people come and talk to me, especially about my interests, I really light up and feel energized. Sometimes the Sims who come here on Getaways will ask me questions, and I'll realize I maybe am social. But I wasn't the right kind of social for the Sim I had feelings for, so...I feel conflicted.\n\nMaybe it matters more right now to try to push myself to share more of who I really am with more people, but maybe if I change myself to be someone that the Sim who rejected me likes, well, I’d be better off."--></T>
        </V>
